Welcome to our 2nd edition of GDG DevFest Setif.

name: Hash Code
description:
1. Form a team (required)
To compete in Hash Code, you must form a team of 2 to 4 people in the Judge System before the start of the Online Qualification Round (February 28th at 17:30 UTC). If you have not formed a team in the Judge System by this time, you will not be eligible to participate in Hash Code. We encourage you to ask around on our Facebook group if youâ€™re still looking for teammates!

2. Solve the practice problem (highly recommended)
We donâ€™t want your team to lose any time during the Online Qualification Round, so please be sure to familiarize yourself with the Judge System before then. If youâ€™d like to practice, there is a practice round with an example problem configured in the Judge System. Check out our Get Ready for Hash Code 2019 video for more information on the Judge System and practice problem.

3. Select a hub (optional)
Want to add a bit of extra fun and excitement to the Online Qualification Round? Compete from one of the 700 Hash Code hubs taking place around the world! You have until the start of the Online Qualification Round to select a hub for your team, but weâ€™d encourage you do this as soon as you can.

PS: Team forming ends on Thursday, Feb 28, 18:30 PM Algeria time and make sure you choose the GDG Setif Hub.
